HEADWORD: Aërolite
<hw>A"⟦eum⟧r*o*lite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>A⟦eum⟧ro-</ets> + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>a⟦eacute⟧rolithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A stone,
or metallic mass, which has fallen to the earth from distant space; a
meteorite; a meteoric stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Some writers limit the word to <xex>stony</xex>
meteorites.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aerolith</ent>⟦br⟧
